Music is more than soundâ€”it's data, emotion, culture, and mathematics woven together. This dataset, Spotify Analysis & Visualization, unlocks a rich world of musical characteristics by bringing together structured track-level metadata and detailed audio features extracted from Spotify. It is designed specifically for data scientists, analysts, ML practitioners, music researchers, and students who want to understand the measurable attributes that shape modern music.

From danceability to acousticness, tempo to valence, each feature offers a unique lens through which you can interpret the essence of a song. Whether your goal is to build a machine learning model, explore musical patterns, create compelling visualizations, or analyze artist trends, this dataset provides a powerful, clean foundation that accelerates your workflow.

ðŸ“˜ Dataset Overview

This dataset consists of track-level records where each row represents a single song. Unlike raw Spotify exports, this dataset is curated, consistent, and structured to support professional-level analysis without requiring additional cleaning or preprocessing.

It combines metadata and audio features into a single, comprehensive resource suitable for a wide range of analytical tasks.
